						               													<description>A tactical level wargame on the battle of Sekigahara at the end of the Sengoku period.&amp;#10;&amp;#230;&amp;#191;&amp;#128;&amp;#233;&amp;#151;&amp;#152; &amp;#233;&amp;#150;&amp;#162;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#182;&amp;#229;&amp;#142;&amp;#159; (Gekitoh Sekigahara) means fierce fight in Sekigahara.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each unit represents 400 soldiers. High lords or generals are included in some units.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players control either the Eastern army (Tokugawa) or the Western army (Ishida and Mori). Each army consists of many clans. Each clan are composed by a lord, generals and soldiers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In each turn, there are opponent's defensive fire step between movement and combat step.&amp;#10;There are two types of combat, fire fight and melee , in both case, basic combat result is morale check. So unit's most important ability is morale.&amp;#10;Not only undermining the troops of their clan, the loss of the lord also decreases army morale. Reduction of army morale reduces it's combat effectiveness.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game includes seven scenarios, two historical and five hypothetical.&amp;#10;Winner is determined by elimination of opponent's highest lord or victory points based on elimination of units.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
